It seems that some people have problems using assist.  Since I've been playing my Enchanter more lately, I have a real desire to see this wrong righted.  If everyone, EVERYONE, does this, there is no end to the mobs we can kill or how far we can go.  If we don't, then we might as well not even have raids.<br>
<br>
1)  What is /assist?<br>
In a battle, selecting a player and pressing /assist will target the mob that he or she is attacking.  If that player is not attacking, you will not target the mob.<br>
<br>
2)  Are there any other things about /assist?<br>
Yes, ABSOLUTELY, glad you asked.  Typing /assist (or macroing it which you SHOULD DO) can be dangerous.  Whenever there is a raid, there is generally a main assist and a secondary assist.  Typing /assist Colubridae will ALWAYS assist Colubridae (or any other player whos name you put there).  THIS IS THE PREFERRED USE OF /ASSIST!<br>
<br>
3)  Will I auto-attack if I /assist?<br>
That's a matter for configuration.  You can choose either.  In the eqclient.ini file (in your Everquest directory), there is an entry that reads: AttackOnAssist=TRUE or AttackOnAssist=FALSE.  The meaning should be self explanatory.  In general, either setting is probably ok, but some chose AttackOnAssist=FALSE because often, on a multiple MOb pull, the puller will switch targets several times.<br>
<br>
4)  The damn puller switched targets on me!<br>
Yep.  That happens, and that's ok.  That's why you NEED to /assist multiple times during the first few seconds of a battle.<br>
<br>
5)  Can't I just see what mob is being attacked and attack it?<br>
Two part answer:  Hell and No.  Many people make this assumption and it simply does not work.  Use /assist PLAYER or go home, period.  On big raids, there are often mobs with the same name clustered in the same fight.  This method is just too dangerous... especially to Enchanters.<br>
<br>
6)  I don't want to type /assist PLAYER all the time.<br>
Fine, macro it.  Go to the small window view (pressing F10), and click on socials.  Pick a social you don't use very often and drag it over to your hotkey sections (that little area where you put keys that pressing numbers activate.  Right click on that button and you can edit the name (call it ASSIST1 or something), and then edit the commands.  Enter /assist PLAYER (and replace PLAYER with the main assist's name).  Then, do the same thing (using a DIFFERENT social key) for the secondary assist.<br>
<br>
7)  Great, thanks for the help Eowen, any other suggestions?<br>
One more that I'll reiterate.  During the opening ten seconds or so  of a battle, press your ASSIST macro several times.  Often, on a multiple mob pull, the main assist will switch targets and not necessarily tell anyone.  While a /shout would help, sometimes it's just not possible.  Pressing your assist macro button several times during the opening seconds of a battle will ensure that you are attacking the right mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
